 {"id":"frankenjax-kdi","title":"End-to-end trace-to-backend tests for multi-equation Jaxprs with linalg + trig mixed programs","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:17:29.624598086Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T17:18:35.812468493Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T17:18:35.812210194Z","close_reason":"Added 6 E2E trace-to-transform tests in fj-api: sin(cos(x)) chain grad, x*exp(x) product grad, x^3+2x^2+x polynomial jit(grad), sin vmap(grad) batch, -exp(x) jit, tanh grad(grad). All exercise make_jaxpr tracing through multi-equation Jaxprs with unary/binary ops and composed transforms.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-l11","title":"Fast-path contiguous dynamic slices","description":"Optimize dynamic_slice for rank-1 and full-trailing row slices by copying contiguous tensor ranges directly while retaining the coordinate fallback for partial inner-axis slices.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T13:01:41.653862581Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T13:06:04.474113390Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T13:06:04.472124973Z","close_reason":"Added contiguous dynamic_slice copy fast path for full trailing row slices, regression coverage, and a baseline benchmark.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-l3zw","title":"Fast-path native F32 scalar control-flow batching","description":"BatchTrace scalar scan/while fast paths currently handle I64 and F64 literals directly but native F32Bits scalar lanes fall back to generic per-element control-flow batching. Add measured native F32 handling for scan/while scalar loops while preserving F32 literal width, add focused parity tests, benchmark before/after, and validate workspace gates.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-28T20:23:58.073208957Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T20:31:49.500889090Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T20:31:49.499059363Z","close_reason":"Fast-pathed native F32 scalar scan/while batching while preserving F32Bits width; benchmarked F32 scan from ~445.8us to ~115.9us and F32 while from ~635.0us to ~84.7us; workspace fmt/check/clippy/test pass on current HEAD.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"frankenjax-l5hb","title":"Harden sort and argsort stride arithmetic","description":"sort/argsort still compute non-empty row-major strides and flat offsets with unchecked usize arithmetic. Harden the path while preserving existing empty-tensor behavior and add targeted coverage.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-29T20:08:51.013004327Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T20:09:16.153004661Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-lbjo","title":"Harden broadcast_in_dim empty-shape strides","description":"eval_broadcast_in_dim computes row-major input strides after recognizing zero-size output shapes. Add a zero-size fast path and use checked stride helpers so empty huge tensor broadcasts do not overflow before returning empty results.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-29T09:50:28.946356378Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T09:52:30.474524412Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T09:52:30.472592374Z","close_reason":"Added broadcast_in_dim zero-size fast path before stride construction, switched non-empty input strides to checked helper, and covered empty huge-shape broadcast","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-lfe","title":"Nested multi-transform compositions: grad(vmap(cond)), vmap(grad(scan)), etc.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-31T03:10:19.356088574Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-31T03:24:49.279520878Z","closed_at":"2026-03-31T03:24:49.279157610Z","close_reason":"Added 11 nested multi-transform composition tests: vmap(grad(cond)), vmap(grad(scan)), jit(vmap(grad(cond))), jit(vmap(grad(scan))), grad(grad(f)), jit(grad(grad(f))), vmap(grad(grad(f))), jit(vmap(grad(grad(f)))), vmap(jit(grad(f))), vmap(grad(while)), plus mixed-predicate variant","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-lh8r","title":"Fast-path literal-left scalar while sub-jaxprs","description":"Extend BatchTrace functional while_loop scalar sub-jaxpr recognition to handle literal-left predicates and bodies (e.g. 10 > x, 0 - x) without falling through to the heavier general active-mask path. Preserve JAX-visible semantics for noncommutative operators, add focused parity tests, benchmark the literal-left case, and validate dispatch/workspace gates.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-28T19:49:55.243630375Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T19:54:52.511091130Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T19:54:52.509296619Z","close_reason":"Fast-pathed literal-left scalar while sub-jaxprs in BatchTrace with reverse operator semantics, focused tests, benchmark evidence, and workspace validation.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
